⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Draygon
node MET · MET · ⟦Draygon:MET:6940a1⟧

WHO   — Draygon — the sea beast
WHAT  — The boss of Maridia in Super Metroid — a great sea beast that seizes Samus in its claws and drags her through the water, slain only by grappling its shattered wall-turrets to turn the room's own current against it.
WHERE — MET · Metroid  Framework inputs: Super Metroid (1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the Space Pirates set guardians over every door to the dark, and Draygon is the last warden between the hunter and the deeper ways of Zebes; it defends its drowned domain as any beast defends its lair.
HOW   — By bulk and speed in the water, by the grip of its claws that snatch and crush, and by the turret-fire of its ruined chamber — answered when Samus grapples the broken turrets and lets the current's charge run through her into the beast.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the warden of the drowned deep — the hunter who would pass Maridia must first pass my claws.

spoken token : dak-rund-sym   ·   hex : 6940a1
